    "text": "FALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD\n04\nWAR… WAR NEVER CHANGES.\nThe 21st century was plagued by the shadow of war. Years of\nconsumption led to shortages of every major resource.\nThe entire world unravelled. Peace seemed a distant memory.\nIn 2077, the hammer fell. In two brief hours, most of the\nplanet was reduced to cinders in atomic fire, forever\nchanging the world as we knew it to the wasteland of today.\nIt is now 2287, and from the ashes of nuclear devastation a\nnew civilisation will struggle to arise. The combatants have\nchanged. But war… war never changes.\nA short drive west of Boston, Massachusetts sits the wreckage\nof what used to be America’s favorite destination spot. Before\nthe bombs fell, Nuka-World was a sprawling amusement park, a\nwonderland of rides and attractions themed around the nation’s\nfavorite soda. Now it’s a hotly-contested wasteland, its park\nlocations carved up between three factions of Wasteland Raiders:\nThe Pack model themselves after the animal kingdom, valuing\nstrength, loyalty, and ferocity above all else. Their colorful\noutfits and animal masks make them stand out amid the\nWasteland's dust.\nThe Operators focus on profit, stealth, and efficiency. They\nappreciate the importance of looking sharp, and they make\nextensive use of flashy, high-tech weapons.\nThe Disciples revel in violence, bloodshed, and torture. They\nclad themselves in dark leathers and metal armor, loving few\nthings as much as the sound of serrated steel separating sinew\nand skin.\nAn uneasy truce exists between the upper echelons of the three\nfactions, but in the lower ranks it’s all-out war. Crews band\ntogether, rallying around charismatic leaders and battling for\nevery inch of valuable ground so that they can prove themselves\nand rise up the ranks.\nWELCOME TO NUKA-WORLD"
