    "page": 12,
    "text": "12\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | 02: Building Blocks\nCREW ROSTER GAME SHEET EXAMPLE\nCREWS AND MODELS\nDuring a game, each player controls a crew made up of around\na dozen models. Each model in a crew comes from the same\nFaction (such as the Disciples, the Pack, or the Operators). All\nof the rules for a Faction and its models are gathered together in\na Faction List (which can be found in Appendix 2).\nWhen the rules refer to a Friendly model, this is any model\nfrom the same crew as the model in question. Similarly, any\nreference to an Enemy model refers to a model from a different\ncrew, even if they’re from the same Faction. Times are turbulent\nin Nuka-World!\nTHE CREW ROSTER\nEach player has a Crew Roster, which is made up of two sheets.\nThe Game Sheet acts as a quick reference during play, and\nrecords all the information about the models in a player’s crew.\nThe Story Sheet tracks the crew’s progress between games; it is\nfully explained in Chapter 04 \"Telling a Story\", pg. 37.\nTHE GAME SHEET EXPLAINED\nThe top of the Game Sheet has an area for basic information\nabout the crew (A) – what their name is and which Faction\nthey’re a part of, as well as their player’s name and how many\ngames they’ve played with the crew. There’s also a section that\nrecords the crew’s Tier and Reputation (B), which gives a\nrough measure of how dangerous they are.\nThe top section also contains a rundown of the crew’s Chems (C)\nand Stash (D), which are explained later.\nThe main body of the Game Sheet features a list of Model\nEntries (E). Each row is an entry for a single model, listing all\nof the information that will be needed to use that model during\na game. The information for a model is divided into two parts:\ninformation about the model itself, and information about the\nmodel’s weapon(s). A Model Entry comprises both parts.\n♥\nNAME (CLASS)\nS\nP\nE\nC\nI\nA\nL\n♥\nWEAPON\nTYPE\nTEST\nTRAITS\nCRITICAL\nPERKS\nSTASH\nCAPS\nPARTS\nCREW TIER\nREPUTATION\nTEMPORARY\nREPUTATION\n1\n2\n3\nRAD-X\nPSYCHO\nNUKA-COLA\nSTIMPAK\nMENTATS\nBUFFOUT\nJET\n5\n6\n8\n9\n15\n10\n11\nCREW NAME\nCREW FACTION\nPLAYER NAME\nGAMES PLAYED\nUP-\nGRADE\nRATING\nB\nC\nD\nE"
