    "text": "21\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | 02: Building Blocks\nHarm Tokens\nAMOUNT OF DAMAGE INFLICTED IS …\nOUTCOME\n… at least double the model’s Endurance\nThe model is Incapacitated\n… equal to or greater than the model’s\nEndurance\nThe model suffers an Injury and\none Harm\n… less than the model’s Endurance\nThe model suffers one Harm.\nIf this causes Excess Harm, the\nmodel suffers an Injury\nCONFUSION\nCombat is chaos! When bullets start flying and people start\ndropping, it’s not easy to keep a cool head!\nWhenever a model is Incapacitated, the controlling player\nmakes a Confusion Test (2I) for each Friendly model that\nwas within 3\" of it. This distance should be checked before\nthe model is removed from play. They make these Tests one\nmodel at a time, in an order of their choice.\n★\tIf the model Passes the Test, it remains where it is.\n★\tIf the model Fails the Test, it becomes Confused. The\ncontrolling player must choose: the model takes Fatigue,\nor the model flees and is removed from play. Exhausted\nmodels that become Confused cannot take Fatigue, so\nthey must flee.\nNote that Confusion is only caused by models being\nIncapacitated. Models that are removed from play for other\nreasons (such as fleeing) do not cause Confusion.\nExperience: Harsh Lessons\nIf a Champion is Incapacitated its crew earns an Experience\nPoint (see pg. 38). A crew can only benefit from this rule once\nper game.\nINJURY\nInjuries are significant wounds that risk taking a model out of\nthe battle. Whenever a model suffers an Injury, mark one of the\nInjury Boxes on its Roster Entry with a pencil.\nIf the number of marked Injury Boxes equals the model’s\nHealth value, the model is Incapacitated. Most Grunts only have\n1 Health, so a single Injury is enough to Incapacitate them.\nHARM\nHarm represents minor wounds and weariness, which make a\nmodel more likely to be injured by a subsequent attack.\nTo show how much Harm\na model has suffered, place\na Harm Token next to it\nshowing the relevant value.\nMost models have a Harm\nLimit of 3. This means that\nthe model cannot suffer any\nmore than 3 Harm.\nAny Harm beyond this is Excess Harm, and has no effect unless\na rule specifically states otherwise.\nSome rules allow models to Recover Harm, reducing the\namount they have suffered. When a model Recovers Harm,\nadjust its Harm Token accordingly.\nDAMAGE\nAttacks and other hazards can inflict an amount of Damage on a\nmodel. When this happens, consult this table below to determine\nthe outcome. Outcomes are detailed below the table.\nINCAPACITATION\nWhen a model is Incapacitated, it is immediately removed\nfrom play."
