    "page": 22,
    "text": "22\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | 02: Building Blocks\ngalactic zone\nEXAMPLE TWO\nEXAMPLE ONE\nDAMAGE EXAMPLES\nThese examples carry on from the ones on pg. 16. Let’s see how\nthose attacks worked out.\nGAME STRUCTURE\nA game of Fallout: Factions takes place over a fixed number of\nRounds determined by the Scenario being used. In each one,\nplayers will take Turns activating models to make Actions,\nmoving them around the Battlefield, and making attacks.\nROUNDS\nEach Round consists of a series of Turns, alternating back and\nforth between the crews. The crew with the Initiative Token\ntakes the first Turn in the Round, then their opponent, and so on.\nAt any point, a player can decide to Pass instead of taking their\nTurn. They might have run out of things to do, or it may suit their\nstrategy to pass early. Once a player has Passed, they will not\ntake any more Turns in the Round; instead, the other crew takes\nany number of remaining Turns, one after the other, and then the\nRound ends.\nAt the start of each game, a number of Round Tracker Tokens\nare placed next to the Battlefield. At the end of each Round, the\nlowest-numbered Token is flipped face-down. If there are no\nface-up Tokens left, the game ends and a winner is determined.\nTaking a Turn\nDuring a crew’s Turn, it is referred to as the Active crew, and\nits player as the Active player.\nAt the start of the Turn, the Active player picks one of their\nmodels that is not Exhausted. This is referred to as the Active\nmodel until the end of the Turn.\nThe Active player makes one or more Actions with the Active\nmodel, as described below. Once they do not wish to make any\nmore Actions, the Turn ends, and the other crew takes their’s.\nThis continues until the Round ends.\nPete's Psycho, Karve, attacked Sophie's Scavver, Eddie, with\na Machete, scoring 4 Hits. The Attack Rules will be explained\nlater; for now, you only need to know that this inflicts 4\nDamage on the Target.\nPete consults the table, comparing the number of Hits to\nEddie’s Endurance, which is 4. This means that the second\nresult on the table applies – “the amount of Damage inflicted\nis equal to or greater than the model’s Endurance” – so the\nScavver suffers an Injury and one Harm.\nEddie only has one Health, so as soon as Sophie marks the\nfirst Injury Box, the model is Incapacitated and removed\nfrom play. If she has any other models within 3\", she’ll have\nto make Confusion Tests for them.\nSophie’s Waster, Slick Rick, has returned fire at Karve. It\nwasn’t a great shot, and she only scored 2 Hits.\nSophie consults the table, using Karve’s Endurance of 4, and\nsees that the third result applies: “the amount of Damage\ninflicted is less than the model’s Endurance”. This means\nKarve takes one Harm; not enough to take him out of the\nfight, but better than nothing!\nTIMING\nSome rules are resolved “at the start of a Round” or “at the\nend of a Round”.\nRules that are resolved at the start of a Round happen\nimmediately before the crew with the Initiative Token\ntakes their first Turn. Rules that are resolved at the end of\na Round happen immediately after the player who did not\nPass finishes their final Turn (but before the Round Tracker\nToken is flipped).\nIf more than one rule takes effect at the same time, they\nare resolved in an order chosen by the player who currently\nholds the Initiative Token."
