    "text": "25\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | 02: Building Blocks\nADVANCED RULES\nCHEMS\nThe Wasteland is littered with potent Chems that a crew can\nput to use when they need a boost. Players have the chance\nto purchase Chems before a game, and can also find them\nduring play by making Rummage Actions (see pg. 26). Each\ndose of Chems can then be used to grant a single one-off bonus,\ndetermined by their type.\nChems are either Common or Rare. Rare Chems cannot be\npurchased before a game and are not easy to obtain. Instead, they\nmust be found during Rummage Actions or through special rules.\nThe available Chems are summarized below. The full versions of\ntheir rules can be found on pg. 70.\nSome Chems are Rare, meaning they cannot be purchased before\na game. Instead, they must be found during Rummage Actions or\nthrough special rules.\nMARKING CHEMS\nAt the top of the game sheet, there is a section to show the\ncrew’s current supply of available Chems. A crew can only have\nup to three doses of each Chem per game, so each entry has\nthree boxes.\nAvailable doses of Chems are marked with a single diagonal\nline. When a Chem is spent during play, a second diagonal line is\nadded to the box, to form a cross.\nFor example, the image below shows that the crew has one\navailable dose of Jet, and has already spent its one available dose\nof Mentats.\nUSING CHEMS\nA player can only use a Chem if their crew has at least one\navailable dose (i.e., a box with a single diagonal mark, as\nexplained above).\nSCAVENGING THE WASTELAND\nNuka-World is scattered with the detritus of a forgotten age, so\nscavenging is a part of everyday life.\nEach Scenario instructs players to set up\nSearch Tokens across the Battlefield. These\nTokens cannot be moved once they have been\nplaced, however they are ignored entirely for\nthe purposes of Visibility and Movement.\nDuring a crew’s Turn, the Active model can\nmake a Rummage Action if it is Unengaged\nand within 1\" of a Search Token.\nCHEM\nCOST PER DOSE\nEFFECT\nRad-X\n5 Caps\nAllows a model to ignore the effects of\nRadiation Tokens.\nPsycho\n6 Caps\nGrants 2 Bonus Dice to an Attack Test.\nNuka-Cola\n8 Caps\nTemporarily increases a model’s Control\nArea by 3\".\nStimpak\n9 Caps\nAllows a model to Recover up to 2 Harm.\nMentats\n10 Caps\nPrevents a model from Failing a\nConfusion Test.\nBuffout\n12 Caps\nLets a model count its Endurance as 2\npoints higher when targeted by an attack.\nJet\n15 Caps\nAllows a model to Recover 1 Fatigue.\nPsycho Jet\nRare\nGrants 2 Bonus Dice to an Attack Test,\nand lets the Attacking model Recover 2\nFatigue.\nWhiskey\nRare\nIncreases a model’s Strength or Endurance\nby 2 points for the purposes of a single\nTest.\nMed-X\nRare\nIncreases a model’s Health by 1 for the\nrest of the game.\nNuka-Cola Dark\nRare\nTemporarily increases a model’s Control\nArea by 3\" and its Luck by 1 point.\nDay Tripper\nRare\nTemporarily increases a model’s Luck by\n2 points.\nSearch token\n♥\nNAME (CLASS)\nS\nP\nE\nC\nI\nA\nL\n♥\nWEAPON\nTYPE\nTEST\nTRAITS\nCRITICAL\nPERKS\nSTASH\nCAPS\nPARTS\nCREW TIER\nREPUTATION\nTEMPORARY\nREPUTATION\n1\n2\n3\nRAD-X\nPSYCHO\nNUKA-COLA\nSTIMPAK\nMENTATS\nBUFFOUT\nJET\n5\n6\n8\n9\n15\n10\n11\nCREW NAME\nCREW FACTION\nPLAYER NAME\nGAMES PLAYED\nUP-\nGRADE\nRATING\nParrish\nTormentor (Champion)\n6\n5\n5\n5\n5\n6\n3\n3\nHandmade Rifle\nRifle (18”)\n4P\nFast\nSuppress\n(2)\nNatural Leader\n44\nWanda\nButcher\n4\n5\n4\n4\n5\n5\n2\n2\nMarksman’s Hand-\nmade Rifle\nRifle (30”)\n2P\nAim (+3)\nSuppress\n(3)\n30\nJulio\nButcher\n4\n5\n4\n4\n5\n5\n2\n2\nSyringer\nRifle (16”)\n2P\nAim (+2)\nPoison (3)\n28\nVadim\nPsycho\n5\n3\n4\n4\n3\n4\n2\n1\nLight Handmade Rifle\nRifle (12”)\n3P\nBladed\nSuppress\n(1)\n20\nOnyx\nPsycho\n5\n3\n4\n4\n3\n4\n2\n1\nPipe Revolver\nHand Weapon\nPistol (12”)\nMelee\n3A\n3S\nAim (+1), CQB\nFast\nPierce\n-\n21\nSlide\nPsycho\n5\n3\n4\n4\n3\n4\n2\n1\n10mm Pistol\nMachete\nPistol (10”)\nMelee\n3A\n4S\nCQB, Fast\n-\n-\nMaim\n21\nAnna\nPsycho\n5\n3\n4\n4\n3\n4\n2\n1\nShort Hunting Rifle\nRifle (14”)\n3P\n-\nPierce\n15\nBogan\nScavver\n4\n4\n4\n3\n4\n4\n2\n1\nRanger’s Hunting\nRifle\nRifle (18”)\n3P\nAim (+1), Bladed\nPierce\n23\nEllis\nWaster\n4\n3\n3\n3\n3\n3\n1\n1\nPipe Revolver\nHand Weapon\nPistol (12”)\nMelee\n3A\n3S\nAim (+1), CQB\nFast\nPierce\n-\n14\nRamona\nWaster\n4\n3\n3\n3\n3\n3\n1\n1\n10mm Pistol\nHand Weapon\nPistol (10”)\nMelee\n3A\n3S\nCQB, Fast\nFast\n-\n-\n15\nX\n 231\n19\nSLAUGHTERHOUSE TEN\nDISCIPLES\nPLAYER NAME\nRAD-X\nPSYCHO\nNUKA-COLA\nSTIMPAK\nMENTATS\nBUFFOUT\nJET\n5\n6\n8\n9\n15\n10\n11"
