    "page": 31,
    "text": "31\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | 03: Getting Started\nCREATING YOUR CREW\nWhen you play Fallout Factions, you control the same crew from\ngame to game, charting its journey and watching its story develop.\nFirst, though, you need to put it together!\nYou need both pages of the Crew Roster,\nwhich can be found on pg. 73 or downloaded\nat www.modiphius.net. Your Crew Roster is\na living document, and will be updated both\nduring and after a game, so you should use a\npencil rather than a pen when filling it out.\nOnce you have your Crew Roster ready, follow the steps here to\ncreate your Crew.\n1. CHOOSE A FACTION\nAppendix 2 (pg. 54) features five Faction Lists, detailing the\nDisciples, the Pack, and the Operators! The first step in creating\na crew is to choose one of these.\nYou may want to choose the one that best suits your play style, or\nthe one whose aesthetic appeals the most, or your favorite from\nthe video game. The choice is yours!\nOnce you’ve chosen a Faction, think of a suitably impressive\nname for your Crew. You can fill in some basic information on\nyour Roster (Crew name, Crew Faction and player name) at the\ntop of your Game Sheet. All new Crews start at Tier 1, so mark\nthe “Tier 1” box, as shown.\n2. RECRUIT MODELS\nNow you can choose models to add to your crew. Any models you\nchoose at this stage are a permanent part of your crew until they\ncome to a sticky end during play, so choose wisely!\nTurn to the Model Classes section of your chosen Faction List to\nsee the options available to you. If you need a reminder of the\ninformation in a Model Class entry, turn to pg. 13. Remember,\nwhen choosing a model, you must pick one of its available\nWeapon Sets, because this will determine the model’s Rating.\nLIMITATIONS\nBefore starting to choose models, read the “Crew Creation”\nsection of your Faction List. This section notes any special\nlimitations or requirements when creating a new crew, you must\nabide by the following limitations:\nOne Leader\nThe first Model Class in each Faction List is a Leader Class. A crew\nmust include exactly one model of this Class – no more, no less.\nChampion Limit\nYou cannot have more Champions than the Champion Limit given\nin the Crew Limits section of your Faction List. As your crew\nwill be Tier 1, use the value in the Tier 1 column. For example, a\nstarting Pack crew cannot have more than three Champions.\nGrunt Limit\nYou cannot have more than five Grunts for every Champion in\nyour crew. For example, if you have two Champions in your crew,\nyou can have up to ten Grunts.\nRating Limit\nThe total Rating value of all of the models in your crew cannot\nexceed 250.\nMODEL ENTRIES\nWhen you add a model to your crew, copy its Profile and the\nProfile(s) of the weapon(s) it is carrying into an empty Model\nEntry row on the Game Sheet of your Crew Roster.\nIf the model is carrying two weapons, copy both of them across.\nUse the upper half of the row for one weapon, and the lower half\nof the row for the other.\nYou may find it useful to figure out the composition of your crew\non scrap paper before you start copying information across to\nyour Crew Roster.\n3. FINISHING TOUCHES\nThe total Rating value of all the models in your crew is its\nReputation. Write this in the Reputation box at the top of your\nGame Sheet. This is used to measure your crew up against your\nopponent’s whenever you play a game.\nThe previous chapter focused on what happens during\na game. This chapter explains how to create a crew, then\nintroduces Scenarios and pre-game Setup.\n♥\nNAME (CLASS)\nS\nP\nE\nC\nI\nA\nL\n♥\nWEAPON\nTYPE\nTEST\nTRAITS\nCRITICAL\nPERKS\nSTASH\nCAPS\nPARTS\nCREW TIER\nREPUTATION\nTEMPORARY\nREPUTATION\n1\n2\n3\nRAD-X\nPSYCHO\nNUKA-COLA\nSTIMPAK\nMENTATS\nBUFFOUT\nJET\n5\n6\n8\n9\n15\n10\n11\nCREW NAME\nCREW FACTION\nPLAYER NAME\nGAMES PLAYED\nUP-\nGRADE\nRATING\nParrish\nTormentor (Champion)\n6\n5\n5\n5\n5\n6\n3\n3\nHandmade Rifle\nRifle (18”)\n4P