    "page": 33,
    "text": "33\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | 03: Getting Started\nSCENARIOS\nEach game of Fallout: Factions uses a Scenario as a framework,\nrepresenting a specific type of encounter between two crews.\nThe Scenario Listings can be found in Appendix 1, starting on pg. 43.\nEach Scenario Listing gives the following information:\nOVERVIEW\nThis section gives a brief summary of the Scenario, so both\nplayers know what to expect.\nIt shows an annotated map of the Battlefield, highlighting any\nspecial areas or Locations (such as the areas where each crew\nwill be set up). It also shows how many Rounds the battle will\nlast, and which player starts with the Initiative Token.\nThere may be additional sub-sections, giving details of unique\nTerrain Features, Objective, or Search Tokens.\nSTARTING POSITIONS\nThis section shows how each player sets up their models at the\nstart of the game.\nMost Scenarios provide Setup Areas for each crew. When placing\na model in a Setup Area, it must be positioned so that its whole\nBase is within the bounds of the area.\nSPECIAL RULES\nAny remaining special rules that apply to the Scenario are\nlisted here.\nSCENARIO DETAILS\nThis section details how the winner of the Scenario is\ndetermined, and may contain other information relating to the\ncrews’ Objectives.\nIn addition, it lists any Outcomes that take effect in the Story\nPhase (as detailed in the next chapter).\nPREPARING TO PLAY\nWhen setting up a game, players should follow the steps listed here:\n1. NOMINATE LEADERS\nEach crew has a default Leader – a model with the Natural\nLeader Perk. If they do not have such a model, they must choose a\nChampion from their crew to act as the Leader for this Mission.\nIf they do not have any Champions, they must nominate a\nGrunt instead.\n2. CHOOSE LOCATION\nNuka-World is split into five parks, each of which is hotly\ncontested by the Factions and their crews: Galactic Zone, Dry\nRock Gulch, Safari Adventure, World of Refreshment, and Kiddie\nKingdom. The Wasteland around the parks isn’t part of the\nongoing turf war, but many battles still take place there.\nEach player makes a Strategy Test (3I) for their Leader. The\nplayer who scores the most Hits chooses a Location for the game –\neither one of the five parks, or the Wasteland. If both players score\nthe same number of Hits, the game takes place in the Wasteland.\n3. DETERMINE SCENARIO\nRoll a die and look up the score on the table below to determine\nwhich Scenario to use for the game.\nSCORE\nRESULT\n4 or less\nThe crew with the lower Reputation chooses a Scenario,\nand is the Attacker.\n5-7\nPlay the Skirmish Scenario.\n8 or more\nThe crew with the higher Reputation chooses a Scenario,\nand is the Attacker.\nTEMPORARY REPUTATION\nDuring Setup, some effects temporarily increase or decrease\na crew’s Reputation. Whenever this happens, the temporary\nvalue is recorded in the crew’s Temporary Reputation box.\nWhile there is a value in this box, it is used in place of the\ncrew’s Reputation. Temporary Reputation only lasts until the\nend of the game, after which the box is cleared.\nTIED REPUTATION\nIf the rules ever refer to the crew with the higher or lower\nReputation, and both Reputation values are tied, the players\nRoll Off. The loser’s Reputation temporarily decreases by 1\n(this should be marked in the Temporary Reputation box).\nFirst Time in the Park?\nIf either of the crews has not played any games before (i.e.,\nthe “Games Played” value on its Crew Roster is 0), skip to\nstep 4; the game automatically takes place in the Wasteland,\nand uses the Skirmish Scenario."
