    "page": 34,
    "text": "34\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | 03: Getting Started\nDesigner’s Note: custom battlefields\nChoosing a Scenario\nIf the Skirmish Scenario hasn’t been chosen, the Attacker chooses\na Scenario. They must pick from the table below, based on the\nLocation where the game is taking place.\n★\tIf the game is taking place in the Wasteland, only Skirmish\nand Ambush Scenarios are available. The Ambush Scenario\ncan only be chosen if the Defender’s Reputation is at least 50\npoints higher than the Attacker’s.\n★\tIf the Defender has this Location marked as their Home Turf\n(see pg. 44), the Skirmish, Stockpile Raid, Retrieval Run,\nLand Grab, and Rumble Scenarios are available.\n★\tIf the Defender has more Control (see pg. 39) in this Location\nthan the Attacker, the Skirmish, Stockpile Raid, Retrieval\nRun, and Land Grab Scenarios are available.\n★\tIn any other Park Location, the Skirmish and Rumble\nScenarios are available. Both players should read the\nScenario Listing before continuing to the next step.\n4. SET UP THE BATTLEFIELD\nThe players now create a Battlefield for the game, following\nthe guidelines below. Before doing so, check whether the\nScenario has any special instructions regarding the setup of\nTerrain Features.\nTHE WASTELAND ENEMY HOME\nTURF\nHOSTILE\nLOCATION\nOTHER PARK\nLOCATION\nSkirmish\nX\nX\nX\nX\nStockpile Raid\nX\nX\nRetrieval Run\nX\nX\nLand Grab\nX\nX\nRumble\nX\nX\nAmbush\nX\nPlace Major Features\nThe players Roll Off, and the winner places a Major Terrain\nFeature (see pg. 10).\nThen the other player places another Major Feature, at least 3\"\naway from the first. This continues back and forth, with players\nmaking sure that there is always at least 3\" between Features.\nAfter placing a Feature, a player can declare that they will not\nplace any more. The other player may then place one final Major\nFeature if they wish.\nPlace Minor Features\nThe player who did not place the last Major Feature now places\nup to two Minor Features anywhere on the Battlefield. Once they\nhave done so, the other player does the same. This continues back\nand forth, until a player declares that they have placed enough\nMinor Features; the other player can then place up to two more.\nUnlike Major Features, Minor Features do not have to be placed 3\"\napart. They can be placed on top of Major Features, if it is possible.\nPlace Objective Tokens and Loot Tokens\nNext, the players place any Objective Tokens and Loot Tokens,\nfollowing the instructions in the Scenario Listing.\nOptional: Place Decorative Features\nIf the players wish, they can add Decorative Features to the\nBattlefield. Remember that they have no impact on the rules, so\nplayers can add as many or as few as they wish.\n5. PREPARE CREWS\nEach player now assembles their crew for the game. If any models\nfrom a crew have a check in the Absent box on the Crew Roster,\nthey do not take part in this game, and should be set aside.\nThe guidelines in this section are just that – guidelines.\nThey’ll create a more-or-less balanced Terrain Setup, which\nwill provide a fun game. However, if both players agree, they\ncan ignore the guidelines entirely and create something\nmore thematic! You could recreate the broad plaza in front of\nGrandchester Mystery Mansion, lay out an evocative tangle\nof wreckage straight out of the Nuka-World Junkyard, or\ndo anything your imagination allows! Creating beautiful\nBattlefields is a big part of the hobby for some players, and\nthey shouldn’t feel constrained by these guidelines.\nThe most important thing to remember is that a game of\nFallout Factions is at its best when there are lots of places for\nmodels to hide, and plenty of Terrain that breaks up lines of\nsight. Big, open Battlefields lead to uninteresting games.\nScout: Scenario Choice\nBefore the die is rolled, either player can declare that they\nwill spend up to 3 Scouting Points (see pg. 41) from the\ngame’s Location. The player with the higher Reputation\ndecides first, then their opponent.\nFor each point spent by the crew with the higher Reputation,\nincrease the score on the die by 1. For each point spent by\nthe crew with the lower Reputation, decrease the score by 1."
