    "text": "35\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | 03: Getting Started\nEXAMPLE : THE LEG-UP\n6. THE LEG-UP\nFor every full 50 points of difference in the crews’ Reputations,\nthe crew with the lower value receives a Bonus Ploy and\nincreases its Temporary Reputation by 50. A crew can receive up\nto three Bonus Ploys in this way. Bonus Ploys come into effect\nin step 8.\nIf there is still a difference in Reputations after Bonus Ploys have\nbeen allocated, the crew with the lower value receives a Chem\nBudget in Caps equal to the difference. This will be used in the\nnext step.\n7. PURCHASE COMMON CHEMS\nEach player can now purchase Common Chems for use in the\ngame. Each player does this in secret, then both players reveal\ntheir choices at the same time.\nWhen purchasing Chem dose, mark a single diagonal line in the\nfirst available box for that Chem on the Roster, as described on\npage 25, and reduce the crew’s Caps Stash by the amount shown\nafter the Chem’s name. Remember that once all three boxes are\nmarked, no more doses of that Chem can be purchased.\nIf a crew received a Chem Budget in the previous step, this\ngrants them bonus Caps which can be used to purchase Common\nChems. Any unused Chem Budget is lost.\n8. STARTING POSITIONS\nPlayers follow the instructions in the Starting Positions section of\nthe Scenario Listing.\nOnce this is done, each player takes a number of Ploy Tokens\nequal to their crew’s Tier, plus one for each Bonus Ploy they\nreceived in the Leg-Up.\nSetup is now complete, and the first Round begins.\nSitting Out\nPlayers can declare that some of the models in their crew\ncan Sit Out the game, as though they were Absent. A player\ncannot do this if it will mean that fewer than half of the\nmodels on their Crew Roster (rounding down) will take part\nin the game.\nAny models that are Sitting Out do not count towards the\ncrew’s Reputation, so their Rating(s) should be deducted,\nand the Temporary Reputation box should be updated. Note\nthat absent models should have already been taken into\naccount. The player with the Initiative must declare if any\nof their models are Sitting Out first, then the other player\ndoes the same.\nScout: Repositioning\nThese rules are on pg.27.\nThe Evolved (Reputation 296) are facing off against the\nNuka City Scions (Reputation 240).\nThe difference in their Reputations is 56. This means the\nScions receive a Bonus Ploy, and their Temporary Reputation\nbecomes 290. They then receive a Chem Budget of 6 Caps."
