    "text": "37\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | 04: Telling a Story\nTHE STORY SHEET\nAll of the games of Fallout: Factions that a crew plays are\nlinked together, following an ongoing narrative arc. During crew\ncreation, the player fills in the Crew’s name, as well as the Crew\nLimits section (A). After their first game with the crew, they will\nbe prompted to choose a Quest Line from their Faction List, and\nfill in the Tier One Quest section (B). This tracks long-term Goals,\nand is explained below.\nAt the same time, they write a value into one of the boxes of the\nCrew Territory section (C). This tracks how well-established the\ncrew is in each of the five Nuka-World Locations, and is used\nwhen choosing Scenarios.\nIn subsequent games, the crew can earn Experience Points, which\nhave their own section (D) on the Story Sheet. The Story Sheet\nalso contains a blank space, which the player can use to make\nnotes and record ongoing grudges…\nQUEST LINES\nEach crew has a Quest Line, which is chosen after its first\ngame. This gives a selection of long-term Goals, which the crew\ngradually completes over the course of multiple games.\nA Quest Line is broken into three Quests, each corresponding to\na separate Tier. The crew’s first challenge is to complete the Goals\nfor the Tier 1 Quest. Once they have done so, they are ready\nto progress to Tier 2, which opens up some new advancement\nopportunities and unlocks the next part of their Quest Line.\nCompleting the Tier 2 Quest lets the crew advance to Tier 3.\nCompleting the Tier 3 Quest completes the Quest Line, and\nfinishes the crew’s story! The Leader has proven that they are\ninvaluable to the future of Nuka-World, and they are raised to\nthe upper echelons of the park along with their chosen followers!\nThe crew disbands, and can’t be used in any more games, but its\nplayer has the chance to found a new crew around some of their\nfavorite long-serving models, and start over again.\nThis chapter delves into the ways that games are linked together,\nfollowing crews and telling the stories of their slow rise to glory.\nCREW ROSTER STORY SHEET EXAMPLE\nCREW LIMITS\nUPGRADE LIMIT\nCONTROL LIMIT\nCHAMPIONS\nCREW TERRITORY\nHOME\nTURF\nCONTROL\nTOTAL\nLOCATION\nCONTROL\nSCOUT\nGALACTIC ZONE\nDRY ROCK GULCH\nSAFARI ADVENTURE\nWORLD OF REFRESHMENT\nKIDDIE KINGDOM\nEXPERIENCE POINTS\nAVAILABLE\nSPENT\nCREW ROSTER\nCREW NAME\nQUEST LINE\nTIER ONE\n GOALS\nMARK PROGRESS WHEN…\nTARGET\nPROGRESS\nTIER TWO\n GOALS\nMARK PROGRESS WHEN…\nTARGET\nPROGRESS\nTIER THREE\n GOALS\nMARK PROGRESS WHEN…\nTARGET\nPROGRESS\nB\nC\nD"
