    "text": "38\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | 04: Telling a Story\nGOALS\nEach Quest has its own section on the Story Sheet, with a space\nfor each of its Goals.\nEXPERIENCE POINTS\nCrews can earn Experience Points during games, representing\nlessons learned from a dangerous life in the Wasteland.\nExperience: Survival\nAt the end of each game, before the Story Phase begins, each\ncrew earns an Experience Point.\nExperience: Failing Forward\nThe first time in each game that a player Fails a\nS.P.E.C.I.A.L. Test, their crew earns 1 Experience, as\nexplained on this page. A crew can only benefit from this rule\nonce per game.\nExperience: Harsh Lesson\nIf a Champion is Incapacitated, its Crew earns an Experience\nPoint. A crew can only benefit from this rule once per game.\nExperience: Achievement Unlocked\nWhenever a crew completes a Goal, it also earns an\nExperience Point as described to the left.\nExperience: Location Domination\nIf a player has to surrender Control in a Location because\ntheir Control Total is higher than their Control Limit, their\ncrew earns 1 Experience. A crew can only benefit from this\nrule once per Story Phase.\nEach Goal has a Progress Condition, which indicates when\na progress box should be marked for that Goal. In the example\nabove, the player marks one of the Progress boxes each time\nthe crew earns 4 or more Experience Points in a single game.\nProgress Conditions are quite varied – some call for specific in-game\nachievements, while others can be fulfilled before or after a game.\nOnce a Progress box has been marked, this is permanent - even if\nthe Progress Condition ceases to apply.\nACHIEVING A GOAL\nOnce the number of marked Progress boxes for a Goal equals its\nTarget value, the Goal has been achieved, and no more boxes can\nbe marked.\nWhen all of a Quest’s Goals have been achieved, the Quest has\nbeen Completed, and the crew is ready to advance to the next\nTier in the Story Phase (see pg. 39).\nWhen a crew earns Experience Points, they are added to the\n“Available” box on their Story Sheet, as shown above.\nPlayers can spend Experience Points in the Story Phase to purchase\nUpgrades for their models (see pg. 43). Any points that are spent are\ndeducted from the Available box, and added to the Spent box. Each\nScenario lists ways in which crews can earn Experience Points,\nbut there are a number of universal ways of earning them:\nCREW LIMITS\nUPGRADE LIMIT\nCONTROL LIMIT\nCHAMPIONS\nCREW TERRITORY\nHOME\nTURF\nCONTROL\nTOTAL\nLOCATION\nCONTROL\nSCOUT\nGALACTIC ZONE\nDRY ROCK GULCH\nSAFARI ADVENTURE\nWORLD OF REFRESHMENT\nKIDDIE KINGDOM\nEXPERIENCE POINTS\nAVAILABLE\nSPENT\nCREW ROSTER\nCREW NAME\nQUEST LINE\nTIER ONE\n GOALS\nMARK PROGRESS WHEN…\nTARGET\nPROGRESS\nTIER TWO\n GOALS\nMARK PROGRESS WHEN…\nTARGET\nPROGRESS\nTIER THREE\n GOALS\nMARK PROGRESS WHEN…\nTARGET\nPROGRESS\nThe crew earns at least 4 Experience Points in a single game.\n3\nYou choose the Land Grab Scenario.\n3\nYou have at least 50 Caps in your Stash.\n1\nx x x x x x\nx x x x x x\nx x x x x x\nx x x\nx x x\nx x x x x\nSlaughterhouse Ten\nRise to Power\n3\n5\n3\ndry rock gulch\n2\n2\nCREW LIMITS\nUPGRADE LIMIT\nCONTROL LIMIT\nCHAMPIONS\nCREW TERRITORY\nHOME\nTURF\nCONTROL\nTOTAL\nLOCATION\nCONTROL\nSCOUT\nGALACTIC ZONE\nDRY ROCK GULCH\nSAFARI ADVENTURE\nWORLD OF REFRESHMENT\nKIDDIE KINGDOM\nEXPERIENCE POINTS\nAVAILABLE\nSPENT\nCREW ROSTER\nCREW NAME\nQUEST LINE\nTIER ONE\n GOALS\nMARK PROGRESS WHEN…\nTARGET\nPROGRESS\nTIER TWO\n GOALS\nMARK PROGRESS WHEN…\nTARGET\nPROGRESS\nTIER THREE\n GOALS\nMARK PROGRESS WHEN…\nTARGET\nPROGRESS\nThe crew earns at least 4 Experience Points in a single game.\n3\nYou choose the Land Grab Scenario.\n3\nYou have at least 50 Caps in your Stash.\n1\nx x x x x x\nx x x x x x\nx x x x x x\nx x x\nx x x\nx x x x x\nSlaughterhouse Ten\nRise to Power\n3\n5\n3\ndry rock gulch\n2\n2\nEXPERIENCE POINTS\nAVAILABLE\nSPENT\nMARK PROGRESS WHEN…\nThe crew earns at least 4 Experience Points in a single game."
