    "text": "39\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | 04: Telling a Story\nTHE STORY PHASE\nAs soon as a game ends, the Story Phase begins. In this phase,\nboth players resolve the Outcomes of the game and decide what\nhappens with their crew in the period of downtime before their\nnext game. The Story Phase should be resolved while both\nplayers are present. If either player is required to make any dice\nrolls, the other player should witness them. The phase has five\nsteps, which are carried out in order:\n1. TREAT THE WOUNDED\nEach player checks to see whether any of their Incapacitated\nmodels suffer any long-term effects. For each Incapacitated\nmodel, the controlling player rolls a die and looks up the result\non the table below, using the column for a Champion or Grunt\naccordingly. Note that this only applies to Incapacitated models,\nnot models that were removed from play in any other way.\nRolls are made one at a time, in an order of the players’ choice.\n2. RESOLVE STORY OUTCOMES\nEach Scenario lists one or more Story Outcomes. These are\nresolved at this step, following the instructions in the Scenario\nListing.\nAdjusting Control\nThe Story Sheet tracks a crew’s Control in each of the five\nNuka-World Locations. If a Story Outcome causes a crew to gain or\nlose Control in a Location, increase or decrease the value in that box\nof the Story Sheet. A crew’s Control in a Location cannot go below 0,\nor below 1 in the Location that is marked as their Home Turf.\nAfter adjusting a crew’s Control, follow these steps in order:\n1.\t Update the crew’s Control Total box by totalling their\nControl across all five Locations.\n2.\tIf the crew’s Control Total is now higher than their Control\nLimit, they must reduce the Control in one or more Locations\nso that this is no longer the case. If they wish, a player can\neven reduce the Control in the Location where they just\ngained Control. The crew simply doesn’t have the reach to\nControl that much turf until it reaches the next Tier.\n3.\tIf the player wishes, they can change their crew’s Home Turf\nto the Location where they have the most Control.\nSCORE\nCHAMPION RESULT\nGRUNT RESULT\n1\nDead. Remove the model’s\nentry from the Crew Roster.\nDead. Remove the model’s entry\nfrom the Crew Roster.\n2\nSerious Injury.\nThe model suffers a Serious\nInjury, as described below.\nClean Bill of Health.\nThere is no lasting effect.\n3\n4\n5\n6\nClean Bill of Health.\nThere is no lasting effect.\n7\n8\n9\n10\nLesson Learned.\nThe crew earns an Experience Point.\nSCORE\nRESULT\nEFFECT\n1\nWeakened\nThe model’s Strength is penalized.\n2\nImpaired\nThe model’s Perception is penalized.\n3\nDrained\nThe model’s Endurance is penalized.\n4\nShaken\nThe model’s Charisma is penalized.\n5\nConcussed\nThe model’s Intelligence is penalized.\n6\nSlowed\nThe model’s Agility is penalized.\n7 - 10\nResting Up\nMark the Absent box on the model’s Roster\nEntry. It will not be able to take part in this\nStory Phase, or the next game.\nPenalized Statistics\nIt’s possible for one of a model’s S.P.E.C.I.A.L. statistics to be\nPenalized by a Serious Injury. When this happens, reduce\nthe statistic’s value by 1, then write an asterisk (*) in the\nsame box to show that this is a temporary reduction, which\nwill only last until it is recovered by a Recuperate Story\nAction (see pg. 40) or special rule.\nIf a statistic that is already penalized would be penalized\nagain by a Serious Injury, treat the die as having rolled a\n7-10 (Resting Up) instead.\nSerious Injuries\nIf a player’s Champion suffers a Serious Injury, they roll another\ndie and look up the result on the table below.\nExperience: Location Domination\nIf a player has to surrender Control in a Location because\ntheir Control Total is higher than their Control Limit, their\ncrew earns 1 Experience, as explained on pg. 38. A crew can\nonly benefit from this rule once per Story Phase."
