    "text": "40\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | 04: Telling a Story\n3. CLEAR CHEMS\nAll Common Chems are cleared from the crew’s Roster. They’ll be\ngone by the time the next game rolls around.\nIf a player has any Rare Chems on their Roster, they may either\nkeep them or sell them. Each Rare Chem that is sold is cleared\nfrom the Crew Roster, and adds 15 Caps to the crew’s Stash.\n4. MAKE STORY ACTIONS\nTo represent what the they are up to in their downtime between\nfights, each crew can now make two Story Actions. These\nActions don’t involve the other crew at all, so players can work\nthrough them at the same time, but players should make each\nother aware of the Actions they are choosing and witness each\nother’s dice rolls.\nA full list of Story Actions can be found in pg. 40-41.\nAdjusting Story Actions\nSeveral factors can increase or decrease the number of Story\nActions that a crew can make:\n★\tIf a crew Retreated from the battle, the number of Story\nActions it can make is reduced by 1.\n★\tIf a crew fought a battle on its Home Turf, the number of\nStory Actions it can make is increased by 1.\n★\tIf the opposing crew was of a higher Tier, the number of Story\nActions is increased by 1, or by 2 if the opposing crew was two\nTiers higher.\n5. COMPLETE A QUEST\nIf a player has achieved all of the Goals for their current Quest, they\nmay now complete it and advance to the next Tier by spending Caps.\nIt costs 100 Caps to advance from Tier 1 to Tier 2, and 200 Caps to\nadvance from Tier 2 to Tier 3. It does not cost anything to advance\nfrom Tier 3 into retirement, but this is a mandatory step when all of\nthe Tier 3 Quest’s Goals have been completed.\nIf a player wishes to Complete their Quest, they follow these steps:\n1.\t Spend the required number of Caps from the crew’s Stash.\n2.\tCheck the next “Tier” box on the crew Roster.\n3.\tAdjust the Crew Limits section of the Story Page in line\nwith the Crew’s new Tier (as shown on their Faction List).\n4.\tCopy the Goals for the next Quest in the Quest Line onto the\nStory Sheet. Alternatively, the player can spend 50 Caps to\nswitch to a different Quest Line available to their Faction,\nand copy across the Goals from the relevant Tier.\nFinishing the Story\nOnce a crew has completed its third Quest, its story is complete.\nIts Leader has carved out a place for themselves amidst the high\nand mighty of Nuka-World, or has perhaps left in search of a new\nadventure. However, the player can create a new Legacy crew\naround one of its Champions, and bring a few Grunts along for\nthe ride. This is explained on pg. 42.\n6. FINISHING TOUCHES\nRecalculate the crew’s Reputation by adding together the Rating\nvalues of all of its models. Do not count any models that are\nmarked as Absent.\nIncrease the “Games Played” count on the Crew Roster by 1.\nThe Story Phase is now complete.\nSTORY ACTIONS\nThis section lists the Story Actions that are available to a crew in\neach Story Phase. A crew can make the same Story Action more\nthan once in a phase, unless a rule specifically states otherwise.\nSTORY ACTION: RECUPERATE\nThe crew spends some time patching up their wounds and taking\nit easy.\nWhen a player makes this Action, they make a Recuperate Test\n(2E) for each Champion in their Crew that has a Serious Injury.\nIf the model Passes the Test, remove one of that model’s Serious\nInjuries as follows:\n1.\t Choose one of its statistics that is marked with an asterisk\n(*). This cannot be a statistic that suffered a Serious Injury in\nthe game immediately preceding this Story Phase.\n2.\tIncrease the Statistic value by 1.\n3.\tRemove the asterisk.\nSTORY ACTION: RECRUIT\nThe crew puts out word that they’re looking for new members.\nWhen a player makes this Action, they can purchase new models\nfor their crew.\nModels are purchased from the crew’s Faction List, spending\nCaps from their Stash for each one equal to its Rating. This\nfollows all of the same rules as purchasing models when creating\na new crew.\nCrew Limits still apply at this stage, and Grunts cannot be\npurchased if they would mean that a crew has more than five\nGrunts for each Champion."
