    "page": 41,
    "text": "41\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | 04: Telling a Story\nSTORY ACTION: BARTER\nThe crew spends some time trading with the locals.\nWhen a player makes this Action, they choose a Location and roll\na number of dice equal to their Control in that Location.\nAdd Caps equal to the highest-scoring die to the crew’s Stash. If\nmore than one die scores equally high, add them together and\nadd Caps equal to the total to the Stash.\nSTORY ACTION: SCOUT\nA crew member heads out to get a good look at a Location.\nWhen a player makes this Action, they choose both a model from\ntheir crew to go scouting, and a Location they will Scout.\nThen they make a Scout Test (2P) for the model. For each Hit,\nthe crew gains 1 Scouting Point in the chosen Location. If the\nmodel Fails, they are waylaid; mark them as Absent.\nThe benefits of Scouting a Location are explained on pg. 27.\nSTORY ACTION: CREW TRAINING\nThe crew works to put what it’s learned to use. When a player\nmakes this Action, they can spend their crew’s Experience Points\nto purchase Upgrades for any of the models that took part in\nthe previous game, except those that are now marked Absent. A\nmodel cannot have more than one Upgrade purchased for it per\nStory Phase.\nThe number of Experience Points that must be spent to purchase\nan Upgrade depends on whether the model is a Champion or a\nGrunt, and how many Upgrades they already have.\nAfter spending the Experience Points, consult the crew’s\nTraining Table (found in their Faction List). Roll two dice and\nchoose one to apply on the Training Table.\nThis shows how the model benefits from the Upgrade. It also\nshows a Rating Increase (depending on whether the model is a\nChampion or Grunt), which must be applied to its Rating as soon\nas the Upgrade is noted on its Crew Roster entry.\nGaining Perks\nWhen a model receives its second, fourth, sixth, or eighth\nUpgrade, it also gains a Perk.\nTo add a Perk to a model, consult the list of Perks on pg. 71-72,\nchoose one, then add it to the Perks box on the appropriate model's\nCrew Roster entry.\nEach Perk lists a Requisite S.P.E.C.I.A.L. value. (For example,\n“Strength 4”.) A Perk can only be chosen for a model that has at\nleast that value in the given S.P.E.C.I.A.L. statistic. If a model\nhas a Serious Injury, the reduced value is used when purchasing\nnew Perks; however, a Serious Injury does not prevent a model\nfrom using Perks it already has, even if it does not currently meet\nthe Requisite S.P.E.C.I.A.L. value.\nSTORY ACTION: MODIFY WEAPONS\nThe crew spends some time tinkering in the workshop.\nWhen a player makes this Action, they can spend Parts from\ntheir crew’s Stash to modify the weapons carried by their models.\nThey can modify any number of weapons, but no weapon can be\nmodified more than once, and weapons carried by a model that\ndid not take part in the game cannot be modified.\nThe Weapons of the Wasteland Appendix (pg. 63-67) contains a full\nlist of weapons arranged by Type. Each weapon entry shows both\nits Profile and a list of Modifications that can be purchased for it.\nSTATISTIC LIMITS\nA model’s Strength, Perception, Endurance, Charisma,\nIntelligence, or Agility cannot be raised higher than 9. A\nmodel’s Luck cannot be raised higher than 5.\nA model’s Health cannot be Upgraded more than once.\nIf a statistic is rolled when it is already at its maximum\nvalue, that die can be Re-rolled.\nEXISTING UPGRADE\nCHAMPION\nGRUNT\n0\n3\n2\n1 - 2\n4\n3\n3 - 4\n5\n4\n5\n6\n5\n6+\n7\n6\nUpgrade Limits\nEach time an Upgrade is purchased for a model, increase\nthe Upgrades value on its Crew Roster entry by 1. A model\ncannot have any more Upgrades purchased for it if it already\nhas Upgrades equal to the crew’s Upgrade Limit.\nTYPE\nTEST\nTRAITS\nCRITICAL EFFECT\nPARTS\nRAITING\nPistol\n(10\")\n3A\nCQB, Fast\nPistol\n(14\")\n2\n+4\n4A\n4\n+6\nSuppress (1)\n2\n+5\n10MM PISTOL\n“The workhorse of any self-respectin’\nRaider, the 10mm does all you need\nit too, but not much more. Easy\nenough to tinker with though, which\nis fun.”"
