    "page": 42,
    "text": "42\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | 04: Telling a Story\nCREATING LEGACY CREWS\nWhen a crew completes its Tier 3 Quest, it disbands as the Leader\nfinds their place among the upper echelons of Nuka-World, or\nheads out to seek their fortune elsewhere in the Wasteland. The\ncrew can no longer be used, but the controlling player can\nchoose to create a Legacy Crew and continue its story with a\nnew Quest.\nCreating a Legacy Crew follows the standard process for\ncreating a custom crew, but the player can include a small\nnumber of models from the Parent Crew (the one that has\ncompleted its Tier 3 Quest).\nWhen choosing models for the new crew, the player can choose\nup to one Champion and up to two Grunts from the Parent\nCrew. Each one is copied to the new Crew Roster and Caps\nequal to their Rating are deducted from the new crew's Budget.\nParticularly experienced models can really eat into a new\ncrew’s budget, and can leave them outnumbered for their first\nfew games, so players should consider this carefully!\nIf a Champion is copied across, the player can choose to give\nthem the Natural Leader Perk. If they do this, the player\ncannot include any other models that have the Natural Leader\nPerk in the crew. (For example, if a Disciples player copies\nacross a Butcher from the Parent Crew and gives them the\nNatural Leader Perk, they cannot also choose a Tormentor.)\nEach Modification amends either the weapon's Type, Test, Traits,\nor Critical Effect. It also shows how many Parts it will cost, and\nhow much a model’s Rating is increased by when the Modification\nis purchased for it.\nModifications can be purchased in any order, but no more than\none Modification can be purchased for a weapon in a single Story\nPhase. A weapon carried by a Champion can have any number\nof Modifications, but a weapon carried by a Grunt is limited to a\nsingle Modification.\nWhen purchasing a Modification, follow these steps:\n1.\t Update the weapon’s Profile accordingly. Underline the\nupdated value on the Crew Roster, to show that it is the\nresult of a Modification.\n2.\tReduce the Parts total in the crew’s Stash by the Parts Cost\nfor the chosen Modification.\n3.\tIncrease the model’s Rating by the Rating Increase value\nfor the chosen Modification."
