    "page": 43,
    "text": "Designer’s Note: Win or Lose, What’s\nthe Difference?\nThis section lists six Scenarios, each of which has its own Setup\ninstructions, special rules and Story Outcomes.\nSCENARIO OVERVIEW\n1: SKIRMISH (PAGE 44)\nIn this Scenario, both crews are looking for a straight-up, no frills\nbattle to gain some glory and Control.\n2: STOCKPILE RAID (PAGE 45)\nIn this Scenario, the Defenders have been tasked with guarding\nsomething valuable and the Attackers are trying to steal it.\nChoose this Scenario if you want to gain some Rare Chems.\n3: RETRIEVAL RUN (PAGE 47)\nIn this Scenario, the Attackers are trying to access secret\ninformation from a series of computer terminals guarded by\nthe Defenders.\nChoose this Scenario if you want to gain some Caps and Parts.\n4: LAND GRAB (PAGE 49)\nIn this Scenario, the Attackers are trying to move on\nthe Defenders’ turf and claim it for themselves.\nChoose this Scenario if you want to steal some\nControl in this Location from the other crew.\n5: RUMBLE (PAGE 50)\nIn this Scenario, the Attackers have called out the Defenders,\nwho need to step up and prove that they’re up to the challenge.\nChoose this Scenario if you want to level the playing field against\nan opponent.\n6: AMBUSH (PAGE 52)\nIn this Scenario, the Attackers have set a trap in a remote\nlocation, hoping to strike a sudden and decisive blow against the\nunsuspecting Defenders.\nChoose this Scenario if you want to catch the other crew at\nits weakest.\nAPPENDIX 1:\nSCENARIOS\nREFERENCE SECTION\nEach Scenario has rules to determine a winner, but it\nmight not always be obvious why it matters. A lot of the\ntime, winning and losing are less important than achieving\nObjectives; both crews can come out of a Scenario having\nachieved what they want. However, some Quest Goals and\nStory Outcomes do require wins, so it’s still important to\nknow who came out on top!\n43\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | APPENDIX 1: Scenarios"
