    "text": "45\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | APPENDIX 1: Scenarios\nTHE DEFENDER\nSTARTS WITH THE\nINITIATIVE TOKEN\nTHE GAME LASTS\nFOR 3 ROUNDS\n6\"\n6\"\n8\"\n4\"\n10\"\n10\"\n4\"\n6\"\n6\"\nDEFENDER\nSETUP\nAREA\nATTACKER\nSETUP\nAREA 4\nATTACKER\nSETUP\nAREA 3\nATTACKER\nSETUP\nAREA 1\nATTACKER\nSETUP\nAREA 2\n36\"\n24\"\nSCENARIO 2: STOCKPILE RAID\nOVERVIEW\nThe player who chose this Scenario is the Attacker. The other\nplayer is the Defender. The Defender has been tasked with\nprotecting some valuable items by the higher-up members of\ntheir Faction. The Attacker needs to find and retrieve them – but\nonly the Defender knows their true location.\nOBJECTIVE TOKENS\nOnce Terrain has been set up, the Defender places all six\nObjective Tokens on the Battlefield with their lettered side face-\ndown. The Tokens marked “Objective A” and “Objective B” are\nthe Attacker’s actual Targets, and the others are just decoys. The\nAttacker must not know which is which.\nAn Objective Token cannot be placed within 8\" of another\nObjective Token, or in a place that a model cannot reach.\nSEARCH TOKENS\nAfter Objective Tokens have been set up, the players take Turns\nplacing a Search Token on the Battlefield, starting with the\nDefender, until three Tokens have been placed.\nA Search Token cannot be placed within 3\" of an Objective Token,\nor within either crew’s Setup Area.\nSTARTING POSITIONS\nThe Defender splits their models into two groups: the\nGuards (who will start the game on the Battlefield) and their\nReinforcements (who will be set up in one corner at the end\nof the first Round). Each group must contain a Champion if\npossible, and both groups must have as equal a number of models\nas possible. Then they set up the Guards within the Defender\nSetup Area, then take the Initiative Token. The Attacker chooses\nup to two of the Attacker Setup Areas, and sets up their models\nwithin the chosen area(s).\nSPECIAL RULES\nTHE TARGET OBJECTIVES\nIf an Attacking model moves within 1\" of an Objective Token, flip\nit over to reveal its letter. If it is any Objective other than A or\nB, remove it from play. If Objective A or B is revealed, a Target\nObjective has been found. Once both Target Objectives have\nbeen found, remove any remaining Objectives from play.\nIf a model from either crew is within 1\" of a revealed Target\nObjective at the start of a Get Moving Action, the Active player\ncan declare that they will carry the Objective. Once a player has\nmoved and completed the Action, move the Objective Token from\nits original position until it is in contact with the model's Base.\nThe Token should be in contact with the part of the model's Base\nthat is closest to where the Token was previously situatied. This\nrepresents the objective being carried or dragged behind the\nmoving model.\nRetrieving the Objective\nIf an Attacking model ends an Action in one of the Attacker Setup\nAreas, and it carries a Target Objective during that Action, the\nmodel and Objective Token are removed from play (this does not\ncount as the model being Incapacitated). The Objective has been\nretrieved, and the Attacker gains 5 points."
