    "page": 50,
    "text": "50\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | APPENDIX 1: Scenarios\nEITHER PLAYER\nCOULD STARTS\nWITH THE INITIATIVE\nTOKEN\nTHE GAME LASTS\nFOR 4 ROUNDS\n18\"\n18\"\n5\"\nDEFENDER'S\nHALF\nATTACKER'S\nHALF\nKILL\nZONE\n24\"\n36\"\nOVERVIEW\nThe player who chose this Scenario is the Attacker. The other\nplayer is the Defender.\nIn this Scenario, the Attacker has challenged the Defender to a\nshowdown in an evenly-matched arena fight.\nTERRAIN\nBefore setting up Terrain, place an Objective Marker in the\ncenter of the Battlefield. No Terrain can be placed within 5\" of it.\nThis area is the Kill Zone.\nORIENTATION\nOnce Terrain has been set up, the players Roll Off. The winner\nchooses which half of the battlefield is the Attacker’s half and\nwhich is the Defender’s half, as shown above.\nSEARCH TOKENS\nAfter Objective Tokens have been set up, the players take turns\nplacing a Search Token on the Battlefield, starting with the\nDefender, until four Tokens have been placed.\nAll Search Tokens must be placed in the Kill Zone, at least 2\"\naway from any other Search Tokens.\nSTARTING POSITIONS\nTo form their Rumble Team, each player chooses models from\ntheir crew with a combined Rating of no more than 120. Their\nother models are Spectators.\nOnce this is done, players must deploy their Rumble Team.\nStarting with the Attacker, the players take turns placing the\nmodels from their Rumble Team one at a time in their own half.\nModels cannot be placed in the Kill Zone, or within 8\" of a model\nfrom the opposing crew. Whoever finishes placing their models\nfirst takes the Initiative Token.\nOnce both Rumble Teams have been placed, the player with the\nInitiative Token places their Spectators in their half, within\n2\" of the Battlefield edge. Then the other player does the same.\nMark all Spectators as Exhausted.\nSPECIAL RULES\nBIG PRIZES\nWhenever a model makes a Rummage Action, roll an extra die.\nDiscard the one that scores the lowest.\nLEVEL PLAYING FIELD\nAt the start of the game, Level Playing Field rules are in effect.\nWhile these rules are in effect, Spectators cannot take any\nActions or recover Fatigue in any way (their Fatigue Tokens are\nnot removed at the end of a Round). They also cannot be targeted\nby any Attacks.\nProving Your Mettle\nEach player tracks the total Rating values of their Incapacitated\nmodels. If one side’s total reaches or exceeds 60, the other crew\nhas Proven Their Mettle, and the Level Playing Field rules\nimmediately cease to apply. Each player makes a React Test (2I)\nfor each of their Spectators; if the test is Passed, flip the model’s\nFatigue Token to its Weary side.\nSCENARIO 5: RUMBLE"
  },
