    "page": 51,
    "text": "51\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | APPENDIX 1: Scenarios\nSCENARIO DETAILS\nThe game lasts for four Rounds, or until a crew Retreats.\nSCENARIO POINTS\nOnce the game has ended, each crew scores points as follows:\n★\tIf a crew Proved Their Mettle, they score 5 points.\n★\tIf a crew Retreated, roll a die. The other crew scores that\nmany points.\n★\tEach crew scores 1 point for each Enemy model that was\nIncapacitated.\n★\tThe crew that scores the most points wins the game.\nSTORY OUTCOMES\nThe winner rolls four dice and adds that many Caps to their Stash.\nIf the Attacker won, they also gain 2 Control in this Location.\nIf a crew Proved Their Mettle, they can make a free Recruit Story\nAction in the Story Phase after this game.\nSPECIAL PLOY: CREEP UP\nWhile Level Playing Field rules are in effect, either player\ncan enact this ploy at the start of their turn: Before choosing\nan Active Model, the player moves each of their Spectators\nup to 3\"."
