    "text": "52\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | APPENDIX 1: Scenarios\nTHE ATTACKER\nSTARTS WITH THE\nINITIATIVE TOKEN\nTHE GAME LASTS\nFOR 5 ROUNDS\nATTACKER\nSETUP\nAREA\nDEFENDER\nSETUP\nAREA\n24\"\n36\"\n18\"\n12\"\n6\"\nCENTER LINE\na Defending model.These models cannot be Repositioned with\nScouting Points. Once this is complete, the Attacker takes the\nInitiative Token.\nSPECIAL RULES\nPANICKED VOLLEY\nBefore the first Round begins, the Defender can pick up to 3\nmodels in their crew to attempt an opening Volley as they realize\nthey are under attack.\nThey make a Volley Test (2I) for each chosen model. If the Test\nis Passed, the model can immediately make an Open Fire Action.\nNo models can give supporting fire during this Action.\nNote that these models take Fatigue as normal, so they will be\nWeary when the first Round begins.\nCOME RUNNING!\nAt the start of the second Round, the Defender rolls a die for each\nmodel in their Reinforcements. On a score of 6-10, they can set\nthe model up within 3\" of their short edge of the Battlefield. On\na score of 1-5, the model is Delayed and does not arrive. It should\nbe set aside again.\nAt the start of the third Round, the Defender sets up any Delayed\nmodels within 3\" of their short edge.\nSCENARIO 6: AMBUSH\nOVERVIEW\nThe player who chose this Scenario is the Attacker. The other\nplayer is the Defender. The Attacker's crew is springing a trap\non the unsuspecting Defender whose crew is out scavenging in\nthe Wasteland surrounding Nuka-World.\nORIENTATION\nOnce Terrain has been set up, the Attacker chooses one short\nBattlefield edge to be their Setup Area.\nSEARCH TOKENS\nThe players take Turns placing Search Tokens, starting with the\nAttacker, until six have been placed.\nA player cannot place a Search Token in their own Setup Area,\nwithin 6\" of another Search Token, or [within 6\" of] an edge of the\nBattlefield.\nSTARTING POSITIONS\nThe Defender picks one of their Champions and up to five\nGrunts to be their Scavenging Party. Then they roll a die for\nevery other available model in their crew. On a roll of 1-2, the\nmodel must Sit Out this game. On a roll of 3-6, the model is set\naside as Reinforcements. On a roll of 7-10, the model joins the\nScavenging Party.\nThe Defender sets up their Scavenging Party in their Setup\nArea, then the Attacker sets up their crew in their Setup Area.\nPlayers can then can spend Scouting Points to have their models\nlie in wait elsewhere on the Battlefield. Setting up models this\nway costs 2 Scouting Points per model, and said model can then\nbe set up anywhere on the Battlefield that is not within 8\" of"
