    "text": "63\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | APPENDIX 3: Weapons of the Wasteland\nEach weapon in this section is shown as a table with multiple\nrows. The top row shows the weapon’s default Profile, and each\nadditional row is an available Modification. The order they are\npresented in is irrelevant; players can choose any Modification\nfrom those available. The table shows the number of Parts that\nmust be spent for each Modification, as well as the amount by\nwhich the model’s Rating must be increased. Weapon Modification\ncan only be applied once per weapon, as described on pg. 41.\nMELEE WEAPONS\nTYPE\nTEST\nTRAITS\nCRITICAL EFFECT\nPARTS\nRATING\nMelee\n3S\nWind Up\nSuppress (1)\n4S\n2\n+5\nTYPE\nTEST\nTRAITS\nCRITICAL EFFECT\nPARTS\nRATING\nMelee\n4S\nMaim\n5S\n2\n+6\nTYPE\nTEST\nTRAITS\nCRITICAL EFFECT\nPARTS\nRATING\nMelee\n5S\nWind Up\nPierce\nMaim, Pierce\n4\n+8\nTYPE\nTEST\nTRAITS\nCRITICAL EFFECT\nPARTS\nRATING\nMelee\n3S\nFast\n-\n4S\n3\n+4\nMaim\n3\n+4\nAPPENDIX 3:\nWEAPONS     WASTELAND\nREFERENCE SECTION\nOF\nTHE\nThis section lists all of the weapons in Nuka-World, and\nshows how each one can be Modified (see pg. 41).\nDEATHCLAW GAUNTLET\nHAND WEAPON\nBASEBALL BAT\nMACHETE\n“You tell me what’s scarier: a\n700-pound murder-lizard, or the\nwhack-job that kills one and straps\nits claw to their hand to cut up\npeople? I know my answer.”\n“Sometimes you gotta use what you\ngot: a knife, a brick, a bit of jagged\nmetal, or a good ol’ rusty pipe. All are\nequally decent at knockin’ someone\ndown when they don’t see it comin’.”\n“Something special about a well-\nmade bat, ain’t there? It’s more than\njust a piece of wood in a fancy shape.\nSure, it’s simple, but it’s a stone-cold\nclassic.”\n“You just can’t beat the classics. It\nchops, it lops, and it's real easy to\nclean. A good Machete’ll make quick\nwork of anyone or anythin’ you plant\nit in.”"
