    "text": "70\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | APPENDIX 4: Reference\nor within 1\" of the Target point if the Weapon also has the Area\n(X\") Trait.\nOne & Done\nOnce this weapon has been used to make an attack, it cannot be\nused again for the rest of the game.\nSlow\nA model can only make one Attack Action with this weapon\nper Round.\nStorm (+X)\nWhen making an Attack Action with this Weapon, add X Bonus\nDice if the Target is within half of the weapon’s Effective Range.\n(For example, if the weapon has the Rifle (10\") Type, the Attack\nwill gain X Bonus Dice if the target is within 5\").\nUnwieldy (X)\nIf a model makes an Attack Action with this weapon and its\nStrength is lower than X, the Attack Test cannot gain any\nBonus Dice.\nWind Up\nWhen making an Attack Action with this weapon, add two Bonus\nDice instead of one if the Active model moved into Engagement\nwith the Target this turn.\nCHEMS\nThis section gives the full rules for each type of Chem (see pg. 27).\nCOMMON CHEMS\nRad-X (5 Caps)\nYou can spend a dose of Rad-X when one of your models ends\nyour Turn within 3\" of a Radiation Token. Until the end of the\nRound, the model does not suffer a penalty to its Endurance as\nthe result of any Radiation Tokens.\nPsycho (6 Caps)\nYou can spend a dose of Psycho when creating the dice Pool for an\nAttack. Add 2 Bonus Dice to the Pool.\nNuka-Cola (8 Caps)\nYou can spend a Nuka-Cola at the start of an Action made by one\nof your models. Until the end of your Turn, the model’s Control\nArea is treated as being 3\" larger.\nStimpak (9 Caps)\nYou can spend a Stimpak at the start of your Turn. When you do,\nthe Active model immediately recovers up to 2 Harm.\nMentats (10 Caps)\nYou can spend a dose of Mentats when one of your models Fails a\nConfusion Test. The model counts as having Passed the Test instead.\nBuffout (12 Caps)\nYou can spend a dose of Buffout when one of your models is\ntargeted by an Attack Action, after the Test Pool has been created\nbut before it is rolled. Increase the model’s Endurance by 2 until\nthe Attack has been resolved.\nJet (15 Caps)\nYou can spend a dose of Jet at the start of your Turn, before choosing\nan Active model. Remove one Fatigue from one model in your crew.\nRARE CHEMS\nPsycho Jet\nYou can spend a dose of Psycho Jet when creating the Dice Pool\nfor an Attack. Add 2 Bonus Dice to the Pool. At the end of the\nAction, the Active model recovers one Fatigue.\nWhiskey\nYou can spend a dose of Whiskey when making a Strength or\nEndurance Test for a model in your crew. Treat the model’s\nStrength or Endurance as being 2 points higher until the Test\nhas been resolved.\nMed-X\nYou can spend a dose of Med-X at any point during your Turn.\nWhen you do, the Active model’s Health is treated as being 1\npoint higher until the end of the game.\nNuka-Cola Dark\nYou can spend a Nuka-Cola Dark at the start of an Action made\nby one of your models. Until the end of your Turn, the model’s\nControl Area is treated as being 3\" larger, and its Luck is treated\nas being 1 point higher.\nDay Tripper\nYou can spend a dose of Day Tripper before making a\nS.P.E.C.I.A.L. Test for a model. Treat its Luck as being 2 points\nhigher until the end of your Turn."
