    "text": "71\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | APPENDIX 4: Reference\nPERKS\nEach Perk is tied to a S.P.E.C.I.A.L. statistic, and shows a\nRequisite Value in parentheses after its name. A model cannot\nobtain a Perk if its value in the relevant Statistic is lower than\nthe Requisite Value.\nSTRENGTH PERKS\n\nBig Leagues (Strength: 4)\nWhen this model makes a Melee Attack, treat its Luck as being\n1 higher.\nSteady Aim (Strength: 4)\nWhen the Active player declares that this model will make an\nOpen Fire Action with a Rifle or Heavy weapon, and they have\nnot moved this Action, they gain a Bonus Die.\nGrenadier (Strength: 6)\nAdd 3\" to the Range of any Grenade weapons carried by this model.\nIron Fist (Strength: 7)\nAdd this weapon to the model’s Roster Entry:\nWEAPON\nTYPE\nTEST\nTRAITS\nEFFECT\nIron Fist\nMelee\n5S\nFast\nMaim\n\nPERCEPTION PERKS\n\nSniper (Perception: 4)\nWhen this model makes a Ranged Attack with a Rifle weapon,\nthe Target never counts as being Obscured by intervening models.\nPickpocket (Perception: 5)\nWhen this model makes a Back Off Action, the Active player\nmakes a Pickpocket Test (3P) for it. If the Test Passes, the\nopposing player must spend a Chem of their choice from their\nCrew Roster, without using it. The Active player immediately\nadds one dose of the same Chem to their own Roster, if they\nhave capacity.\nIf the Test scores 3 or more Hits, the Active player can choose\nwhich Chem is stolen instead of the opposing player.\nRifleman (Perception: 6)\nWhen this model makes a Ranged Attack and uses a Rifle\nweapon, treat its Luck as being 1 higher.\nAwareness (Perception: 7)\nThis model can give Supporting Fire even if it is not within the\nattacking model’s Control Area. The other restrictions still apply.\nENDURANCE PERKS\n\nRad Resistant (Endurance: 4)\nThis model is unaffected by Radiation Tokens.\nCannibal (Endurance: 5)\nIf a model is Incapacitated while in contact with this model, this\nmodel recovers all Harm.\nToughness (Endurance: 6)\nThe first time each game that this model would be Incapacitated,\nmake a Toughness Test (2E) for it. If it Passes, it immediately\ntakes enough Harm to bring it to its Harm Limit, but remains\nin play.\nLifegiver (Endurance: 7)\nAt the start of each Round, this model recovers 2 Harm.\nCHARISMA PERKS\n\nInspirational (Charisma: 4)\nIncrease this model’s Control Area by 2\".\nLone Wanderer (Charisma: 5)\nWhile this model does not have any other Friendly models within\nits Control Area, add a Bonus Die to any Tests you make for it.\nIntimidation (Charisma: 6)\nWhen the opposing player makes a Confusion Test for an Enemy\nmodel within this model’s Influence, they count its Intelligence\nas one lower.\nCap Collector (Charisma: 7)\nWhen trading Chems for Caps (during a Scavenge Story Action,\nor when clearing Rare Chems after a game), double the number\nof Caps that the crew receives if there is at least one model with\nthe Perk in the crew and it is not marked as Absent.\nINTELLIGENCE PERKS\n\nScrapper (Intelligence: 4)\nWhen this model makes a Search Action, double the number of\nCaps and Parts added to the crew’s Stash.\nChemist (Intelligence: 5)\nIf this model is not Absent at the start of a game, the crew increases"
