    "text": "72\nFALLOUT: FACTIONS – BATTLE FOR NUKA-WORLD | APPENDIX 4: Reference\nits Chem Budget by 5 (even if it has a higher Reputation than the\nopposing crew).\nMedic (Intelligence: 6)\nWhen this model makes a Patch Up Action, it can either remove\nup to 3 Harm from itself, or remove up to 3 Harm from a Friendly\nmodel within 1\".\nIf this model is not Absent when its Crew makes a Recuperate\nStory Action, add a Bonus Die to all Endurance Tests made to see\nwhether Champions recover from Serious Injuries.\nGun Nut (Intelligence: 7)\nIf this model is not marked Absent at the end of the Make Story\nActions step of the Story Phase, you may pay Parts to Modify a\nsingle weapon as though the crew had made a Modify Weapons\nStory Action.\nAGILITY PERKS\n\nBlitz (Agility: 4)\nAfter this model completes a Brawl Action, the Active player can\nmove it up to 3\".\nGunslinger (Agility: 5)\nAdd 4\" to the Effective Range of any Pistols this model is carrying.\nFire and Move (Agility: 6)\nAfter this model completes an Open Fire Action, the Active player\ncan move it up to 4\".\nMoving Target (Agility: 7)\nWhen this model is targeted by an Attack Action, its controlling\nplayer can declare that it will dodge at the start of the Make the\nAttack Test step. A model that dodges takes one Fatigue, but its\nEndurance is increased by 2 until the attack has been resolved.\n(If it also uses Buffout, the effect is cumulative).\nLUCK PERKS\n\nFortune Finder (Luck: 2)\nWhenever this model makes a Scavenge Action, add Caps equal\nto the result of the die roll to the crew’s Stash.\nFour Leaf Clover (Luck: 3)\nWhen Fortune Smiles on a S.P.E.C.I.A.L. Test for this model, add\ntwo Standard Dice to the roll instead of one.\nBloody Mess (Luck: 3)\nIf an attack made by this model Incapacitates an Enemy model,\neach other Enemy model within 2\" takes 1 Harm. Excess Harm\nhas no effect.\nINNATE PERKS\nSome Perks are Innate. These Perks cannot be gained by\nany models that do not start with them.\nNatural Leader\nThis model automatically Passes Confusion Tests. When\nmaking an Intelligence Test for a Friendly model within\nthis model’s Control Area, you can choose to use this model’s\nIntelligence value instead of the model’s own value.\nWhen choosing a Leader at the start of a game, this model\nmust be chosen if it is possible to do so. If there is more than\none model with this Perk in the crew, the player must choose\none of them.\nGrim Reaper’s Sprint (Luck: 4)\nIf an attack made by this model Incapacitates an Enemy model, and\nat least two Luck Dice scored Hits, this model recovers one Fatigue.\nCREW ROSTER\nThe rosters on the following pages can be photocopied for\npersonal use. Downloadable versions are available at\nwww.modiphius.net."
